<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1021,1498]" box="[160,480,1021,1047]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,480,1021,1047]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Justification of the transfer</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1021,1498]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">
Even though we were unable to examine the 
<typeStatus box="[678,729,1057,1082]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">type</typeStatus>
specimen of this species, the original illustrations of epigyne show that it lacks diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[953,1052,1092,1117]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[953,1052,1092,1117]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Sergiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as globose spermathecae, with internal protrusions and blind median ducts (
<bibRefCitation author="Platnick NI &amp; Shadab MU" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref7779" refString="Platnick NI, Shadab MU. 1981. A revision of the spider genus Sergiolus (Araneae, Gnaphosidae). Am Mus Novit. 2717: 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="1981">Platnick and Shadab 1981</bibRefCitation>
); instead, it resembles the species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kamura, 1992" authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[726,968,1161,1186]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[726,807,1161,1186]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Hitobia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kamura T" box="[813,968,1161,1186]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="119 - 132" refId="ref7382" refString="Kamura T. 1992. Two new genera of the family Gnaphosidae (Araneae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica. 41: 119 - 132. doi: 10.2476 / asjaa. 41.119." type="journal article" year="1992">Kamura, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as illustrated for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bosenberg &amp; Strand, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Bosenberg &amp; Strand" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[160,725,1196,1221]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unifascigera">
<emphasis box="[160,388,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Hitobia unifascigera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bosenberg W &amp; Strand E" box="[405,717,1196,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="93 - 422" refId="ref6965" refString="Bosenberg W, Strand E. 1906. Japanische Spinnen. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft. 30: 93 - 422." type="journal article" year="1906">Bösenberg &amp; Strand, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[791,842,1196,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bosenberg &amp; Strand, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Bosenberg &amp; Strand" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[160,605,1230,1255]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">
<emphasis box="[160,277,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">H. asiatica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bosenberg W &amp; Strand E" box="[293,597,1230,1255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="93 - 422" refId="ref6965" refString="Bosenberg W, Strand E. 1906. Japanische Spinnen. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft. 30: 93 - 422." type="journal article" year="1906">Bösenberg &amp; Strand, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
: recurved 
<collectionCode box="[729,773,1230,1255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">AER</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[835,877,1230,1255]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12821" name="City Museum" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" type="Herbarium">PER</collectionCode>
and large sac-like spermathecae (compare 
<bibRefCitation author="Gajbe UA &amp; Gajbe P" box="[394,645,1265,1290]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="99 - 101" refId="ref7241" refString="Gajbe UA, Gajbe P. 1999. New species of spider of the genus Sergiolus Simon from Madhya Pradesh (family: Gnaphosidae). Rec Zool Surv India. 97: 99 - 101." type="journal article" year="1999">Gajbe and Gajbe 1999</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1, 3–4 with 
<bibRefCitation author="Kamura T" box="[834,984,1265,1290]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="119 - 132" refId="ref7382" refString="Kamura T. 1992. Two new genera of the family Gnaphosidae (Araneae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica. 41: 119 - 132. doi: 10.2476 / asjaa. 41.119." type="journal article" year="1992">Kamura 1992</bibRefCitation>
, figs 11, 16, 20, 25). Based on these observations, we propose to transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gajbe &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1999" box="[810,1032,1300,1325]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamhetaghatensis">
<emphasis box="[810,1032,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">S. lamhetaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[1069,1150,1300,1325]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1150,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Hitobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Judging from the illustrations of epigyne (
<bibRefCitation author="Gajbe UA &amp; Gajbe P" box="[632,883,1334,1359]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="99 - 101" refId="ref7241" refString="Gajbe UA, Gajbe P. 1999. New species of spider of the genus Sergiolus Simon from Madhya Pradesh (family: Gnaphosidae). Rec Zool Surv India. 97: 99 - 101." type="journal article" year="1999">Gajbe and Gajbe 1999</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1, 3–4), this species may be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tikader &amp; Gajbe, 1976)" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[486,970,1369,1394]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[486,699,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Hitobia poonaensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tikader BK &amp; Gajbe UA" box="[711,963,1369,1394]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="185 - 191" refId="ref8113" refString="Tikader BK, Gajbe UA. 1976. On some new species of spiders of the genus Sergiolus Simon from India (family: Gnaphosidae). Proc Indian Acad Sci. 84: 185 - 191." type="journal article" year="1976">Tikader &amp; Gajbe, 1976</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[977,1106,1369,1394]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but confirmation requires the examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[771,822,1404,1429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">type</typeStatus>
or topotype material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[160,388,1438,1463]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamhetaghatensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[160,388,1438,1463]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">H. lamhetaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[395,523,1438,1463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1021,1498]" box="[192,373,1473,1498]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">
<emphasis box="[192,245,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1155,1557,1687]" box="[160,262,1557,1583]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1155,1557,1687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">
We were unable to trace out the 
<typeStatus box="[526,586,1593,1618]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[621,838,1593,1618]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamhetaghatensis">
<emphasis box="[621,838,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">S. lamhetaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the arachnid collection of ZSI, even though the authors mentioned that the 
<typeStatus box="[718,778,1628,1653]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847">types</typeStatus>
would be deposited there (
<bibRefCitation author="Gajbe UA &amp; Gajbe P" pageId="9" pageNumber="2847" pagination="99 - 101" refId="ref7241" refString="Gajbe UA, Gajbe P. 1999. New species of spider of the genus Sergiolus Simon from Madhya Pradesh (family: Gnaphosidae). Rec Zool Surv India. 97: 99 - 101." type="journal article" year="1999">Gajbe and Gajbe 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
